This just doesn't grab me. It's decently written, but it just doesn't do it for me. I think part of it is that the central theme (the wart-toad connection) is a bit dull for me. It otherwise seems to be a bit all over a the place with warts really being viral, but here being fungal, and leading into amphibians. It just lacks the sort of coherance that makes it sound real and scary. Also, the whole frogs-with-human minds thing feels tacked on. They show little signs of remembering their former lives (minimizing the body horror of being trapped as a frog), and it downplays the infectious nature as the central concept.

No vote for now. I need to mull it over more.







